## 🔧 Full Tech Stack Summary — *Drug or Pokémon? App*

### 🌐 Frontend Stack
| Tool/Library       | Role |
|--------------------|------|
| **Next.js**        | Core React-based web framework for frontend, routing, and API endpoints. |
| **Tailwind CSS**   | Utility-first CSS framework for responsive design following the app's visual identity. |
| **shadcn/ui**      | Component library (built on Radix UI + Tailwind) for accessible UI components like buttons, modals, and inputs. |
| **TanStack Query** | Data-fetching and state management for quiz data, leaderboards, and user achievements. |
| **Zod**            | Runtime schema validation for form inputs and API responses. |
| **Framer Motion**  | Animation library for microinteractions, quiz feedback animations and transitions. |
| **next-auth**      | Authentication for user accounts, leaderboard tracking, and achievement persistence. |
| **Vercel KV / Redis** | Leaderboard storage and rate limiting functionality. |
| **React Hook Form** | Form management for custom inputs and settings. |
| **howler.js**      | Audio library for handling sound effects with toggle functionality. |

---

### 🧠 Backend Stack
| Tool/Library        | Role |
|---------------------|------|
| **Next.js API Routes** | Serverless functions for handling quiz data, user scores, and custom inputs. |
| **Prisma ORM**      | Type-safe database access for user data, achievements, and leaderboards. |
| **PostgreSQL**      | Primary database for storing user data, quiz content, and leaderboard information. |
| **Node.js**         | JavaScript runtime environment for server-side operations. |
| **JWT**             | JSON Web Tokens for secure authentication. |
| **bcrypt**          | Password hashing for secure user authentication. |

---

### 🗄️ Database Schema
| Entity              | Description |
|---------------------|-------------|
| **Users**           | User profiles with authentication details and game statistics. |
| **Questions**       | Database of drug names and Pokémon names for quiz content. |
| **Leaderboard**     | Global ranking table with user scores. |
| **Achievements**    | Predefined achievement templates and user progress tracking. |
| **CustomInputs**    | User-generated content for custom quiz modes. |
| **UserStats**       | Detailed statistics for user performance and streak tracking. |

---

### 🛢️ Database Stack
| Tool / Technology    | Role |
|----------------------|------|
| **PostgreSQL**       | Primary relational database (user accounts, subscriptions, API usage logs, audit trail). |
| **Drizzle ORM**      | Type-safe ORM in the frontend/backend (can be used in server-side Next.js routes). |
| **Prisma or SQLAlchemy (alt)** | Optional: backend-side ORM if FastAPI also writes to DB (or use Drizzle from frontend only). |
| **pgvector (optional)** | If implementing vector similarity search later (e.g., pill shape recognition embedding storage). |

---

### ☁️ Cloud Infrastructure
| Service / Platform   | Role |
|----------------------|------|
| **Vercel**          | Primary hosting platform for Next.js application with integrated CI/CD. |
| **PlanetScale**     | Serverless MySQL platform compatible with Prisma for database hosting. |
| **Vercel Edge Functions** | Optimized global delivery of dynamic content for leaderboards. |
| **Vercel KV / Upstash Redis** | Fast key-value storage for leaderboards and temporary data. |
| **Cloudinary**      | Image hosting for achievement badges, avatars, and visual elements. |

---

### 🛡️ Security & Monitoring
| Tool/Service         | Role |
|----------------------|------|
| **Next-Auth**       | Authentication framework for secure user login. |
| **JWT (JSON Web Tokens)** | Secure, stateless authentication for user sessions. |
| **OAuth (Google/GitHub)** | Social login options for quick user onboarding. |
| **Content Security Policy** | Protection against XSS and data injection attacks. |
| **Sentry**          | Error tracking and performance monitoring. |

---

### 🧪 Testing Stack
| Tool                 | Role |
|----------------------|------|
| **Jest**            | JavaScript testing framework for unit tests. |
| **React Testing Library** | Component testing for UI elements. |
| **Cypress**         | End-to-end testing for user flows and game mechanics. |
| **Mock Service Worker** | API mocking for isolated component testing. |

---

### ⚙️ DevOps & Deployment
| Tool/Service         | Role |
|----------------------|------|
| **GitHub Actions**   | CI/CD pipeline for automated testing and deployment. |
| **ESLint**          | Code quality and style consistency. |
| **Prettier**        | Automated code formatting. |
| **Husky**           | Git hooks for pre-commit linting and testing. |
| **Vercel Preview Deployments** | Preview environments for each pull request. |
| **Dependabot**      | Automated dependency updates for security. |

---

### 📱 Responsive Design & Accessibility
| Tool/Approach        | Role |
|----------------------|------|
| **Tailwind CSS Responsive Utilities** | Breakpoint-based responsive design. |
| **Radix UI**        | Accessible component primitives. |
| **ARIA Landmarks**  | Semantic HTML and accessibility attributes. |
| **Focus Management** | Keyboard navigation support for all interactive elements. |
| **Contrast Testing** | Tools to ensure WCAG 2.1 compliance for text contrast. |

This tech stack provides a robust foundation for building the "Drug or Pokémon?" app with a focus on performance, accessibility, and engaging user experiences. The combination of Next.js, Tailwind, and modern serverless architecture enables rapid development and scalable deployment.
